quickly get them into your topic.

97
00:04:34,630 --> 00:04:39,650
But I do think, especially for informative speeches, that you don't

98
00:04:39,650 --> 00:04:43,070
want the subject matter to be a mystery.

99
00:04:43,070 --> 00:04:47,270
I want to very quickly within my introduction for an informative speech

100
00:04:47,270 --> 00:04:49,770
let the audience know what I'm talking about.

101
00:04:49,770 --> 00:04:53,680
If someone was taking notes on my presentation, they would know what to

102
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:55,040
write at the top of the page.

103
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:57,450
Oh, he's talking about whatever.

104
00:04:57,450 --> 00:05:03,150
So I want to signal what the topic title is so that people know what I'm

105
00:05:03,150 --> 00:05:05,270
going to be discussing.

106
00:05:05,270 --> 00:05:09,070
Now that opening device is just there to grab attention.

107
00:05:09,070 --> 00:05:11,100
Attention in and of itself might fade.

108
00:05:11,100 --> 00:05:15,850
We want to take that attention once we have it and convert it to interest.

109
00:05:15,850 --> 00:05:20,700
So we're moving from that opening device to a statement of relevance.

110
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:23,980
So basically I want to-- after I've got somebody's attention, I want to

111
00:05:23,980 --> 00:05:28,240
provide a quick explanation of why they should pay attention, why they

112
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:32,870
should continue to devote their mental energies towards what I'm saying.

113
00:05:32,870 --> 00:05:37,790
So I want to think through at least making explicit what that audience can

114
00:05:37,790 --> 00:05:39,840
get out of this presentation.

115
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:45,570
So you might be thinking about formally providing an answer to the

116
00:05:45,570 --> 00:05:47,680
question, why should I pay attention?

117
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:50,050
What am I going to get out of this?

118
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:53,540
Is it a matter of personal impact?

119
00:05:53,540 --> 00:05:55,660
Is this an influential issue?

120
00:05:55,660 --> 00:05:57,980
Is it going to affect the audience's daily life?

121
00:05:57,980 --> 00:06:01,350
Or is there maybe sort of more of a general impact?

122
00:06:01,350 --> 00:06:02,620
It's a common issue.

123
00:06:02,620 --> 00:06:05,780
It affects many people even if it doesn't affect you.

124
00:06:05,780 --> 00:06:10,110
Maybe this issue is going to affect how we think about other things

125
00:06:10,110 --> 00:06:11,550
outside of your topic realm.

126
00:06:11,550 --> 00:06:14,250
Or maybe it's just fascinating in and of itself.

127
00:06:14,250 --> 00:06:18,060
But I think you want to have a sentence or two basically providing

128
00:06:18,060 --> 00:06:22,810
the rationale for why an audience member should pay attention.

129
00:06:22,810 --> 00:06:26,880
So for business presentations, you would sort of open up the presentation

130
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:29,960
and then probably talk about how your subject matter affects the

131
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:34,910
organization or perhaps some other divisions here at this company.

132
00:06:34,910 --> 00:06:40,150
For research presentations, you might say, well, this is how this issue,

133
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:44,160
what I'm going to be presenting on, affects our collective understanding

134
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:49,310
of another research idea or of future research possibilities.

135
00:06:49,310 --> 00:06:53,550
So I want to grab the audience's attention, opening device.

136
00:06:53,550 --> 00:06:57,830
I want to convert that attention into interest through sort of explaining

137
00:06:57,830 --> 00:06:59,700
why someone would want to pay attention.

138
00:06:59,700 --> 00:07:02,780
And then I want to just orient the audience to how we're going to be

139
00:07:02,780 --> 00:07:04,380
spending our time together.

140
00:07:04,380 --> 00:07:07,610
So we've done this in the impromptu speech through a formal preview of

141
00:07:07,610 --> 00:07:08,610
your main points.

142
00:07:08,610 --> 00:07:10,700
I think you still want to do that here.

143
00:07:10,700 --> 00:07:13,190
It doesn't have to be overly formal.

144
00:07:13,190 --> 00:07:17,460
And different settings are going to call for different types of previews.

145
00:07:17,460 --> 00:07:21,550
But I just think you want to be able to say to the audience, I'm going to

146
00:07:21,550 --> 00:07:24,580
carve up our time into three general domains.

147
00:07:24,580 --> 00:07:28,800
One thing you might also consider doing in this orientation phase of the

